snippet.title: Avengers: Doomsday - First Trailer (2026) Marvel Studios
snippet.description:
‚Äî Attention Viewers ‚ö†Ô∏è
‚Äî This is a Fan-Made Concept Trailer for:
‚Äî Avengers: Doomsday

‚Äî Music Credits - https://youtu.be/6Ot-gRruxng

‚Äî This video is a fan-made concept trailer, created solely for artistic and entertainment purposes.The goal behind this trailer is to showcase my creativity and storytelling skills through a concept trailer based on a unique and original idea. By combining various effects, sound design, and AI technologies, I‚Äôve crafted a cinematic experience that reimagines familiar worlds in bold and imaginative ways. This trailer is not official and is intended to entertain, inspire, and engage with the YouTube community. Thank you for your support ‚Äî now let‚Äôs dive into a world shaped by creativity and craft. üé¨‚ú®

‚Äî In this concept trailer for Avengers: Doomsday, the story centers on the long-unresolved consequences of Steve Rogers‚Äô final choice in Endgame, revealing that his decision to remain in the past fractured reality in ways the Avengers never anticipated. As timelines splinter and the stability of the main MCU begins to erode, Steve is forced back into the conflict, confronting the personal cost of his legacy and the ripple effects of his sacrifice. The narrative hints at a corrupted alternate reality where familiar heroes took darker paths, drawing Doctor Doom into the heart of the multiversal crisis and threatening total collapse across worlds. With time itself no longer trustworthy, Rogers emerges as both the cause and the possible solution, facing a reckoning that could determine whether the prime timeline survives or is rewritten forever.

‚Äî  Subscribe to Teaser Universe üé¨
‚Äî  For inquiries: teaseruniverse@gmail.com üì©

snippet.title: Vrusshabha Official Trailer (Malayalam) | Mohanlal | Naandda Kishore | 25th December 2025 Release
snippet.description:
#Vrusshabha #Mohanlal #VrusshabhaTrailer #RoarOfVrusshabha #VrusshabhaOn25thDecember #Nandakishore  
#EktaKapoor #SamarjitLanketsh #Raginidwivedi #Nayansarika #ConnekktMedia #BalajiTelefilms #AbishekSVyasStudios #AashirvadCinemas  #TSeriesSouth #TSeries #lalettan #SamCS #ResulPookutty #MalayalamFilm #TeluguFilm 

Presenting: The official Trailer of VRUSSHABHA - Malayalam 

Malayalam | Telugu | Hindi | Kannada

Vrusshabha is an epic that is high on storytelling. It explores the deep and unshakable bond between a father and son, a bond that faces an unexpected test. Spanning two worlds and timelines from the grandeur of a historic kingdom to the intensity of the modern era the film takes audiences on a powerful journey of love, sacrifice, and destiny.
 
Blending heart-stirring drama with breathtaking action, soul-stirring music, and stunning visuals, Vrusshabha is crafted to be an unforgettable big-screen experience. With Mohanlal portraying a king for the very first time in a bilingual epic, this film promises to leave a lasting impact long after the credits roll.

 Vrusshabha is a grand Pan Indian film shot simultaneously in Malayalam and Telugu, and dubbed in Hindi and Kannada.

Starring:Mohanlal, Samarjit Lankesh, Nayan Sarika, Ragini Dwivedi, Ajay, Neha Saxena, Vinay Varma, Garuda Ram, Ali, Kishore, Ayyappa P Sharma

Vrusshabha is an epic that is high on storytelling. It explores the deep and unshakable bond between a father and son, a bond that faces an unexpected test. Spanning two worlds and timelines from the grandeur of a historic kingdom to the intensity of the modern era the film takes audiences on a powerful journey of love, sacrifice, and destiny.
 
Blending heart-stirring drama with breathtaking action, soul-stirring music, and stunning visuals, Vrusshabha is crafted to be an unforgettable big-screen experience. With Mohanlal portraying a king for the very first time in a bilingual epic, this film promises to leave a lasting impact long after the credits roll.

In this scary story, Franklin meets many ghosts and monsters like Granny, Huggy Wuggy, Mr. Meat, Choo Choo Charles, Ice Scream Rod, and Scary Teacher. To unlock his own mystery container in Indian Bike Driving 3D, Franklin must invite all these ghosts. Will Franklin survive this horror adventure? The album "‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç - Om Sakthi Om is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 3 songs sung by L.R Eswari, Veeramanidasan .

Music By : Kanmani Raja, D.V.Ramani
Produced by Unique Recording
‡ÆÆ‡Øá‡Æ≤‡Øç‡ÆÆ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æµ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡ØÇ‡Æ∞‡Øç ‡ÆÜ‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ™‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ±‚Äå‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡Æü‚Äå‡Æ≤‡Øç‡Æï‚Äå‡Æ≥‡Øç

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All!

Do Like, Share, Comment & Subscribe to Bhakthi Maalai!

‡ÆÆ‡Øá‡Æ≤‡Øç‡ÆÆ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æµ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡ØÇ‡Æ∞‡Øç ‡ÆÜ‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ™‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ±‚Äå‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡Æü‚Äå‡Æ≤‡Øç‡Æï‚Äå‡Æ≥‡Øç

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All!

The album "‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æì‡ÆÆ‡Øç - Om Sakthi Om is dedicated to Goddess Amman. This album has 3 songs sung by L.R Eswari, Veeramanidasan .

Produced by Unique Recording
‡ÆÆ‡Øá‡Æ≤‡Øç‡ÆÆ‡Æ∞‡ØÅ‡Æµ‡Æ§‡Øç‡Æ§‡ØÇ‡Æ∞‡Øç ‡ÆÜ‡Æ§‡Æø‡Æ™‡Æ∞‡Ææ‡Æö‡Æï‡Øç‡Æ§‡Æø ‡Æö‡Æø‡Æ±‚Äå‡Æ™‡Øç‡Æ™‡ØÅ ‡Æ™‡Ææ‡Æü‚Äå‡Æ≤‡Øç‡Æï‚Äå‡Æ≥‡Øç

Amman is the South Indian Goddess of Rain. She is the main South Indian mother/goddess in the southern India. Mari is closely associated with the Hindu goddess Parvati and Durga. 
Her festivals are held during the late summer/early autumn season of Aadi throughout Tamil Nadu and Deccan region, the largest being Aadi Thiruvizha. Devotees offer Pongal that is cooked using earthen pots which are made during the festive season. Rituals such as fire walking and mouth or nose piercing are also practised. Mari in Tamil means rain. Thus she is referred to as Mariyayee or Aathaa. Aathaa means mother or grandmother. She symbolizes sacrifice, motherhood, abundant wealth and good health. 

May Goddess Amman Bless You All!

snippet.title: IQOO S8UL vs GodLike Esports | Grand Finale | Mythic Showdown Season 2 | Moba Legends 5v5
snippet.description:
The Mythic Showdown Season 2 heats up as we enter the Upper Bracket Quarter Finals, where top teams from across India battle it out in intense MOBA Legends 5v5 matchups.

Only the most consistent and strategic squads will secure their place in the Round Robin stage, moving one step closer to the grand LAN finale.

Hosted by War Drum Esports and powered by Vizta Games, the official publisher of Moba Legends 5v5, this tournament represents the next step in developing India‚Äôs competitive gaming ecosystem. The event brings together rising underdogs, established elite teams, and the region‚Äôs most passionate players under one unified platform.


Prize Pool-
Total Prize Pool: ‚Çπ4,00,000 INR + 2,00,000 Diamonds
Rewards will be distributed among winners, finalists, and standout performers, with additional community giveaways for viewers and participants.
Prizepool breakdown and more details about mythic showdown s2 - 


Tournament Format and Roadmap-

Open Qualifiers: 128 teams compete for a chance to prove themselves. The top three teams from this stage qualify for the Wildcard stage.

Wildcard Stage: The Wildcard will feature five elite teams along with three teams that advance from the Open Qualifiers. These eight teams will battle for four qualification slots to the Swiss Stage.

Swiss Stage: The main stage of Mythic Showdown Season 2. It will include ten Mythic teams, two Elite teams, and four Wildcard-qualified teams. All sixteen teams will compete through the Swiss system to qualify for the Round Robin.

Round Robin: The top eight teams from the Swiss Stage will progress to the Round Robin phase, where they will play against each other to determine who advances to the Mythic Showdown Season 2 LAN Finals.

LAN :The final top 4, including the Semi Finals and Grand Finals, will take place offline in Guwahati, marking the grand conclusion of Mythic Showdown Season 2!

The top teams will battle it out on stage, giving their all in the final journey to conquer the throne and etch their names in Mythic history.

Dates to be announced soon ‚Äî stay tuned for the ultimate showdown!

About the Event-
The Mythic Showdown Series is designed to provide players with an opportunity to rise from the community level to the professional stage. Season 2 builds upon the success of previous editions, offering a structured, transparent, and competitive platform for teams to showcase their potential and represent India‚Äôs growing esports scene.



Stay connected for updates and highlights:


YouTube: https://youtube.com/@wardrumgames?
Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/wardrumesports/
Discord: https://discord.com/wardrumgames

Beneath a star
There is a gift
For you and I 

His name is Light
Immanuel

Around the fire
Hoping that it will
keep you warm

manger in your heart
You have no room for love

And rainy days
For all of them
We give Him praise

some on the way
But we‚Äôve learned 
to be okay
